article.headline: Elon University 92, UT-Chattanooga 74
article.story: CHATTANOOGA, Tenn. (AP) -- Montell Watson scored 25 points, hitting 6-of-9 3-pointers, to lead Elon over Chattanooga 92-74 Monday. Elon (6-9, 3-0 Southern Conference) built a 46-34 halftime lead after shooting 58.6 percent before the break. For the game, the Phoenix shot 54.4 percent, including 16-of-30 3-pointers. Chris Chalko added 19 points for Elon, hitting three 3-pointers during a late first-half spurt when the Phoenix stretched their lead from five points to 18. Jackson Atoyebi had 13 points and LeVonn Jordan 12 for the Phoenix. Chattanooga (9-8, 1-2) was led by Charles Anderson with 15 points, including 6-of-7 from the floor. Alphonso Pugh scored 14 and Keddric Mays, Ricky Hood and Jerice Crouch had 10 each. The Mocs, who shot 45.6 percent for the game, got only as close as 46-36 in the second half. Chattanooga's last lead was 8-5 early in the game on a layup by Mays.
